				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$f_{\mathrm{t}}^{({\mathrm{split}})}$$\end{document}, then the loss reduction by branching can be calculated by the difference of the loss, Dscore(ft)=L(t)ft(current)-L(t)ft(split)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
